OL,3,CCare-leavers endured 'lengthy and
OL,4,Coften traumatic' wait for personal data
OL,6,FMr Nicholson, who describes the care
OL,7,Fsystem he grew up in as "broken",
OL,8,Finitially only received 126 pages of
OL,9,Fhis 800-page personal file. It took
OL,10,Fhim almost 25 years to finally access
OL,11,Fthe full truth surrounding his
OL,12,Fchildhood, something he is still
OL,13,Fcoming to terms with.
OL,15,F"Growing up in care, the state became
OL,16,Fmy storyteller, taking on the role
OL,17,Fmost people's families play," he said.
OL,18,F"My files hold many of those stories,
OL,19,Fyet for years they seemed to forget
OL,20,Fwho I was."
