OL,6,FInformation Commissioner John Edwards
OL,7,Fsaid that for too many people the
OL,8,F"fight" to get their records can have
OL,9,F"devastating consequences" and he has
OL,10,Fwritten to local authorities in
OL,11,FEngland, Scotland and Wales, and
OL,12,Fhealth and social care trusts in
OL,13,FNorthern Ireland.
OL,15,FIn his letter to local authorities, Mr
OL,16,FEdwards said frontline council staff
OL,17,Fmust understand how to handle requests
OL,18,Fwith care and communicate with empathy.
