OL,6,FResponding to the research by the ICO,
OL,7,FAmanda Hopgood, the chair of the Local
OL,8,FGovernment Association's Children,
OL,9,FYoung People and Families Committee,
OL,10,Fsaid: "Councils want to ensure people
OL,11,Fhave access to their care records
OL,12,Fwithout delay and to be able to move
OL,13,Fmore quickly on releasing records.
OL,15,F"However, many councils lack the
OL,16,Fresources to do so, as a result of
OL,17,Fhistoric funding pressures. There is
OL,18,Falso the additional challenge of older
OL,19,Frecords being generally paper-based,
OL,20,Fso this can require more work and take
OL,21,Flonger."
